    {
      "question": "A suspension cable of a bridge hangs in the shape of a parabola. The path of the cable is modeled by the polynomial $p(x) = x^2 - 6x + 8$, where $x$ represents the horizontal distance from the left pillar in meters and $p(x)$ represents the height of the cable from the ground in meters. The ground level is represented by the $x$-axis. Observe the parabolic path and answer the following questions.",
      "type": "case_study",
      "marks": 4,
      "questions": [
        {
          "id": "i",
          "type": "mcq",
          "question": "What are the horizontal distances $x$ from the left pillar where the cable touches the ground?",
          "answer": "(C)",
          "options": [
            "(A) $1, 8$",
            "(B) $-2, -4$",
            "(C) $2, 4$",
            "(D) $-2, 4$"
          ],
          "solution": {
            "steps": [
              "Set $p(x) = 0$ for the cable to touch the ground.",
              "Solve $x^2 - 6x + 8 = 0$.",
              "Factorize as $(x-2)(x-4) = 0$.",
              "The roots are $x=2$ and $x=4$."
            ],
            "derivation": "$x^2 - 6x + 8 = 0 \\\\ x^2 - 4x - 2x + 8 = 0 \\\\ x(x-4) - 2(x-4) = 0 \\\\ (x-2)(x-4) = 0 \\\\ x = 2, 4$"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "ii",
          "type": "vsa",
          "question": "What is the coordinate of the vertex of the parabola representing the cable?",
          "answer": "$(3, -1)$",
          "solution": {
            "steps": [
              "The $x$-coordinate of the vertex is $-b/2a$.",
              "Here $a=1, b=-6$, so $x = -(-6)/2(1) = 3$.",
              "Calculate $p(3) = (3)^2 - 6(3) + 8 = 9 - 18 + 8 = -1$."
            ],
            "derivation": "$x = -b/(2a) = 6/2 = 3 \\\\ p(3) = 3^2 - 6(3) + 8 = 9 - 18 + 8 = -1 \\\\ \\text{Vertex} = (3, -1)$"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "iii",
          "type": "mcq",
          "question": "If the cable were shifted upward by $2$ meters, the new polynomial would be $g(x) = x^2 - 6x + k$. What is the value of $k$?",
          "answer": "(B)",
          "options": [
            "(A) $6$",
            "(B) $10$",
            "(C) $8$",
            "(D) $4$"
          ],
          "solution": {
            "steps": [
              "Shifting upward by $2$ units means adding $2$ to the function.",
              "$g(x) = p(x) + 2$.",
              "$g(x) = (x^2 - 6x + 8) + 2 = x^2 - 6x + 10$.",
              "Comparing with $x^2 - 6x + k$, we get $k=10$."
            ],
            "derivation": "$g(x) = p(x) + 2 \\\\ g(x) = x^2 - 6x + 8 + 2 \\\\ g(x) = x^2 - 6x + 10 \\\\ k = 10$"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "iv",
          "type": "vsa",
          "question": "Does the parabola $p(x) = x^2 - 6x + 8$ open upwards or downwards? Justify based on the coefficient of $x^2$.",
          "answer": "Opens upwards because the coefficient of $x^2$ is positive ($a=1 > 0$).",
          "solution": {
            "steps": [
              "A quadratic polynomial is in the form $ax^2 + bx + c$.",
              "If $a > 0$, the parabola opens upwards.",
              "Here, $a=1$, which is greater than $0$."
            ],
            "derivation": "$p(x) = ax^2 + bx + c \\\\ a = 1 \\\\ a > 0 \\\\ \\text{Parabola opens upwards.}$"
          }
        }
      ],
